FBIS3-54378 "drnes017ff_94001" FBIS-NES-94-017 Document Type:Daily Report 26 Jan 1994 South Asian Regional Affairs Members' Tension Not To Affect SAARC Progress BK2001124094 Colombo Sri Lanka Broadcasting Corporation International Service in English 1045 GMT 20 Jan 94 BK2001124094 Colombo Sri Lanka Broadcasting Corporation International Service Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The new secretary general of the South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation [SAARC] has said that tension between member nations will not affect the group's progress. Yadav Kant Silwal, the forum's new secretary general, said at a briefing at the Overseas Correspondents Association in Bangladesh that regional tensions have not affected the other groupings and there is no reason why it would affect SAARC. He said that he saw no reason why contentious bilateral issues should affect SAARC and added that it was prospering despite these (?problems). He had talks with Bangladeshi Prime Minister Khaleda Zia, who is current chairperson of SAARC, on Tuesday [18 January].
